FBIS4-41966 "drsov125_p_94001" FBIS-SOV-94-125 Daily Report 28 Jun 1994 CAUCASUS Armenia Minister: Nagorno-Karabakh `De Facto' Part of Armenia Minister: Nagorno-Karabakh `De Facto' Part of Armenia NC2806191994 Yerevan SNARK in English 2003 GMT 28 Jun 94 NC2806191994 Yerevan SNARK English BFN [Text] Yerevan, 28 June. (SNARK) -- Armenian Internal Affairs Minister, Vano Siradegyan, announced in an interview published today by the "HAYASTANI HANRAPETUTYUN" ("REPUBLIC OF ARMENIA") newspaper that Nagorno-Karabakh has been de facto incorporated in Armenia. Though the region is the place where clash the interests of super- powers, "they cannot ignore the organized nation which is ready to fight", said Mr. Siradegyan. At the same time, the minister opposed the fanning of "military hysteria" in Armenia which, in his opinion,"may discredit the state". The major mission of his department the minister called preservation of political stability in Armenia until the new election campaign. By his words, "Armenia cannot allow itself early elections, forced resignations, and other social shocks".
